body:
@pleerock @holm: I don't think we should close this issue yet. I think having a dry-run option for `typeorm migration:run` is still very useful to have. PR #6978 is not implementing a dry-run option.

Something like the following could print out the queries that will be generated:

```bash
npm run typeorm migration:run --dry
```

It's especially useful when we use the built-in helper functions instead of manually writing SQL:
```js
public async up(queryRunner: QueryRunner): Promise<void> {
    await queryRunner.addColumn('episodes',  new TableColumn({
        name: "date_deleted",
        type: "datetime",
        isNullable: true,
        default: null,
    }));
}
```

For me personally, I just want to be able to print out the resulting queries that will be executed to `stdout` without doing a round-trip to the database. To do a quick sanity check if the resulting series of DDL operations look okay. Maybe it's better to always just write manual queries? ðŸ¤”
